  "Blocking ACE prevents the conversion of angiotensin I to the potent vasoconstrictor angiotensin II; without angiotensin II, blood vessels remain dilated and aldosterone secretion decreases, reducing sodium and water retention and lowering blood pressure. This is exactly how ACE inhibitor drugs work clinically.": ""
